    <chapter>
      <heading>
        Software documentation for the TTIOQuery class
      </heading>
      <class name="TTIOQuery" super="NSObject">
        <declared>TTIOQuery.h</declared>
        <desc>
          Compressed-domain query against an
          TTIOSpectrumIndex. Predicates are combined
          with AND (intersection). The query operates entirely on
          the in-memory index arrays — signal-channel datasets are
          never opened, so a 10k-spectrum scan completes in under
          a millisecond and never touches the encrypted intensity
          stream. Builder-style chaining: NSIndexSet *hits =
          [[[[TTIOQuery queryOnIndex:run.spectrumIndex]
          withMsLevel:2]
          withRetentionTimeRange:[TTIOValueRange
          rangeWithMinimum:600 maximum:720]]
          withPrecursorMzRange:[TTIOValueRange
          rangeWithMinimum:500 maximum:550]]
          matchingIndices]; API status: Stable.
          Cross-language equivalents: Python:
          ttio.query.Query Java:
          global.thalion.ttio.Query
        </desc>
        <method type="instancetype" factory="yes">
          <sel>queryOnIndex:</sel>
          <arg type="TTIOSpectrumIndex*">index</arg>
          <desc>
            <em>Description forthcoming.</em>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="NSIndexSet*">
